original_result.user_prompt: What's VT100 code to render green terminal text?
original_result.completion_text:
The VT100 code to render green terminal text uses the ANSI escape sequence for setting the foreground color to green. In this case, the code is "\033[32m", where \033 represents the escape character, [ sets the color attribute, and 32 specifies the green color.

Here's an example usage in Python:

```python
print("\033[32mThis text will be displayed in green.\033[0m")
```

When executed in a compatible terminal, the output will display the text "This text will be displayed in green." in green color. Note that the "\033[0m" resets the formatting back to default after displaying the colored text. This ensures that only the desired portion of the text appears in green, while other parts remain unaffected by the color change.
